<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/489</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                                to Admiral <persName type="to">Caperton</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Situation as outlined not thoroughly understood. What are grounds of suit
                            in which attachments are issued? If for legitimate debts what is
                            objection to permitting attachment in such case to stand pending final
                            adjudication? Is it possible to attach present pay in suit to collect
                            for discounted arrears of pay, if so, how can current salary be
                            discounted under present method of paying, if so, should not system be
                            further modified? Why will permitting attachments to stand encourage
                            salary discounting? Would the investigation of cause of suit involve
                            such difficulties that all must be recognized or all disregarded?
                            16010.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Josephus Daniels</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>